Subject: Re: [Caml-list] Agda-style parser

Andrej is probably referring to mixfix operators in Agda:
http://wiki.portal.chalmers.se/agda/agda.php?n=3DReferenceManual.Mixfix

To quote:

> A name containing more than one name part can be used as an operator wher=
e the arguments go in place of the _. For instance, an application of the n=
ame if_then_else_ to arguments x, y, and z can be written either as a norma=
l application if_then_else_ x y z or as an operator application if x then y=
 else z.

-anil

